                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.001 Vincent, Stenio/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>237. Stenio Vincent was elected President this afternoon on the fourth ballot and
                    took the oath of office at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
